-Haven't messed with bards/necros really yet<br>
<br>
Epic pet is VERY nice for PvP, it has massive dmg output, and the stun/nuke/higher resists yada yada make your foes die much easier <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12008" target="_blank">Humfrey</a> ~ Arch Mage <Br><i>Vazaelle<Br><i><a href="http://pub37.ezboard.com/bsacredfires63116" target="_blank">Sacred Fires</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugreldek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Greldek</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(11/5/01 5:21:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gnomesig.homestead.com/files/gnome1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How are Mages in PvP?</span><hr size=1> I'll base this off my limited PvP server knowledge, and <br>
my Bluebie dueling knowledge(pretty good)<br>
<br>
<br>
In low levels, mages rock! earth and air pet are the most<br>
usefull pets in duels for along time (although chasing<br>
a mage at high lvls with a backstabbing pet sucks!)<br>
<br>
The higher you get, the more resistance your opponents<br>
will become, reducing the effectivness of your pets:<br>
root and stun (air pets spell)<br>
 Thus taking out melee will be quite a bit more difficult,<br>
because they will most likely be MR'ed up the arse!<br>
