<br>
You as a Magician have months of solo experience. Think of the opponent as a more intelligent version of the prey you usually hunt ... but one with less solo experience than you (except druid and necro).<br>
<br>
The only way a melee or hybrid can win against us is<br>
a) fighting us in a very narrow space where we can't cast on them due to hiding behind a corner or attacking us outright<br>
b) abusing code and cheating us off our pet<br>
<br>
The secret is MOVE! Keep them from hitting you. Kite them, DSed pet trailing. Stand still to Malise and nuke only when they are turning on the pet.<br>
<br>
Against Chanters: If they use a pet, use a fire pet with Sword of Runes, it tears apart the chanter pet quickly and will help you. If they use no pet and hope to charm your pet ... excellent ... do the unexpected, vanish your own pet and nuke away at the chanter.<br>
<br>
Against Wizards ... I haven't really done it ... about level 20 I tried a 23 Wizard and he went OOM before he could kill me (but he had low int). Now I'd send the air pet to stun and thus mana drain him and try to get out of the way until he's helpless.<br>
<br>
Against Necros ... haven't done that, might be the toughest. Pet handling similar to Chanter, probably. The DoTs can be countered with Cancel Magic if done right. Fear might be a problem, high MR may help. Apart from that ... NUKE.<br>
<br>
My impression: There's none better than a Mage at duels, if we have room to move and long range nuke.<br>
<br>
