<br>
1.  They *will* fear your pet.<br>
2.  They *will* take your life faster than you can take theirs, winning the battle with a FULL life bar, if you let it happen.<br>
3.  Fear sticks to pets, but not forever....<br>
<br>
Here's how to win:<br>
<br>
Start off the fight with a sirocco, aimed at their pet.  If they're stupid, they'll catch a wave too, otherwise, it will kill their pet outright.  You should send your pet at theirs before you start casting this.<br>
<br>
At this point their pet is either dead (perfect) or very low, and the necro is probably chaincasting Deflux as fast as he can, or trying to DoT you.  If your resistances don't plain suck, his dot's won't land at all (especially darkness).  Deflux will land almost every time though, it hits you for 203 or so and gives him that life.  You can ignore this while his life is full and you have 1k+ hp left, but if you stay in range you can't hurt him at all and you'll go down fast.<br>
<br>
So, back to the fight...His pet is low / dead, and yours is likely feared at this point.  His pet will attack you (if he's not dumb enough to let it chase your running pet).  Chaincast scars on it, and let it die on your DS.  Now you play the range game.<br>
<br>
Most (all?) necro dots and lifetaps have an effective range of 100 feet, and if the target steps out of range at any time during casting, the spell fails.  Magician bolts (Lava bolt, and more importantly Scars) have a range of 300 feet.....You can probably see it already.  In the time it takes him to cast anything, you can step out of range and fire off a bolt.  Rinse and repeat, once his pet is dead he shouldn't land another spell on you.  Your pet will pop in at random intervals and quad him for something obscene, and he will either fear it or root it and lifetap it.  Doesn't really matter, he can't kill you and your pet on a single bar of mana.  If he does turn his attention to your pet, do NOT burn him down...meditate or something, his life will be full regardless of what you cast on him.  When the pet is dead, cast another one and he is in a world of trouble.  As a 55 mage, I have beaten necros up to 58 (haven't tried any higher) with 100% success, and I've crushed more than one I-Am-God complex ;p<br>
<br>
